main event: Two objects resembling stars, observed changing colors over Linda Vista, California on 9 November 1956.
interesting points: The objects were the size of a dime and exhibited colors that changed between red, green, and white., The observation was classified as AERO-visual., The length of time the objects were in sight is noted as still being in sight., The report originates from Project Blue Book, an official U.S. Air Force investigation into UFOs., There was insufficient data about the course of the objects.
witness description: civilian, specific details about witnesses are not provided
